<span id="Description"></span>
==Beschreibung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:BIM_Shape2DCut.svg|24px]] [[BIM_Shape2DCut|BIM Shape2DCut]] tool creates a 2D projection of only the intersecting faces of selected objects on the XY-plane.
 
This tool is a specialized variant of the [[BIM_Shape2DView|BIM Shape2DView]] tool. It performs the exact same operation, but explicitly sets the resulting object's {{PropertyData|Projection Mode}} property to {{Value|Cutfaces}}.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
When used in combination with an [[Arch_SectionPlane|Arch SectionPlane]], it produces solid filled shapes where the plane physically slices through the 3D geometry. It is typically used alongside BIM Shape2DView to build standard architectural drawings with background lines and solid cut fills.
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Anwendung==

Siehe [[BIM_Shape2DView/de#Usage|BIM Form2DAnsicht]] für den vollständigen Arbeitsablauf. Die Schritte sind identisch, außer beim Aufruf des Werkzeugs über:
#* Die Schaltfläche {{Button|[[Image:BIM_Shape2DCut.svg|16px]] [[BIM_Shape2DCut/de|Schnitt]]}}.
#* Den Menüeintrag {{MenuCommand|Beschriftung → 2D-Ansichten erstellen → [[Image:BIM_Shape2DCut.svg|16px]] Schnitt}}.
* Das Tastaturkürzel {{KEY|V}} dann {{KEY|C}}.

<span id="Notes"></span>
==Hinweise==

Siehe [[BIM_Shape2DView/de#Notes|BIM Form2DAnsicht]].

<span id="Properties"></span>
==Eigenschaften==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
See [[Draft_Shape2DView#Properties|Draft Shape2DView]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''BIM Shape2DCut''' tool alters the following default properties of the created object:
* {{PropertyData|InPlace|Bool}}: Set to {{FALSE}}.
* {{PropertyData|Projection Mode|Enumeration}}: Set to {{Value|Cutfaces}}.
</div>


